Service Agreement and Privacy Policy "Welcome to VPhoneOS! Before you use ours service, please be sure to carefully read and fully understand the terms of the \"Service Agreement\" and \"Privacy Policy\" to help you understand the services we provide you and how we collect and process personal information. We will take corresponding security measures in accordance with legal requirements and try our best to protect the security and controllability of your personal information. Clicking the \"Agree, Continue to Use\" button means that you have agreed to the foregoing agreement and the following agreements. 1. We may apply for system device permissions to collect information such as mobile phone device identification, as well as other device information such as network device hardware addresses and log information to identify the device, and apply for storage permissions to download and cache related files.
2. We may apply for location permissions to complete security services and location-based services (LBS) and other related functions. It is also used to provide APPs in virtual machines for use. When APPs in virtual machines are used, Will reapply.
3. In order to help you complete registration as a VPhoneOS user, real-name authentication account, and provide problem diagnosis and troubleshooting services, we may apply for phone permissions and device permissions. It is also used for APP in the virtual machine. When the APP in the virtual machine is used, it will re-apply to you.
4. In order for the APP in the virtual machine to apply for camera and microphone permissions when needed, we will apply for camera and microphone permissions from you, and the APP in the virtual machine will re-apply to you when using it.
5. The above permissions and sensitive permissions such as camera, microphone, photo album, storage space, GPS, etc. will not be turned on by default or forced to collect information.
6. You have the right to reject this agreement, but without obtaining the necessary authorization and information, we will not be able to provide you with complete services." Agree, continue to use Reject, exit APP

Deleting "Instance " Game " (iOS " " (" ) Input sync (master) Input sync (slave) Introduction: After enabling this feature, you only need to perform touch and click actions on the master instance, and the other slave instances will automatically perform the exact same touch and click actions in the background without requiring manual intervention, eliminating the need to operate each instance individually. \n This feature is particularly suitable for multi-instance scenarios, but all these slave instances must ensure that everything from the interface layout to the app version is exactly the same as the master instance, so that touch and click actions will not be disrupted. \n Therefore, it is strongly recommended to use the snapshot feature of VPhoneOS, which can generate multiple identical instances, making it ideal for input sync feature. Usage: 1. Turn on \"Input sync (master)\" on one instance, the master instance can only have one. \n2. Turn on \"Input sync (slave)\" on other instances you want to be controlled. There can be any number of controlled ends. \n3. First start the master instance, then start several slave instances, and ensure that the screen in these instances are in the same state. \n4. Switch to the master instance and do any touch and click operations, which will automatically synchronize to all slave instances. \n5. If the slave instance is started before the master instance, the input sync may not work correctly. In this case, turn off \"Input sync (master)\" and turn on again will fix it. When the Genshin Impact game needs to be updated, do not update it in the snapshot, but start instance 1 to update. At this time, all the snapshots that depend on instance 1 will be automatically deleted, and you need to repeat the previous steps to create the snapshot again.
